-- India's Reliance Communications falls after launching share sale
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Tue Jun 24, 2014 11:54PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 25 (Reuters) - Shares of India's Reliance Communications Ltd <RLCM.NS> fall 2.2 percent after the company said on Tuesday it is launching a share sale to institutional investors as it looks to reduce debt. [ID:nL4N0P53A7]

The company said it would sell shares for 142.13 rupees each, or a discount of 5 percent to the floor price, but the company did not specify the number of shares being sold in the offering.